CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 6, 1957, pg. 3, reads: "New Brakeman Will Work Here - As one of 300 brakemen at the Conway (Pa.) Yards of the Pennsylvania Railroad, the largest automatic freight classification yards in the world, William R. Pace Jr. was hire recently. He will handle switches, properly display train signals, manipulate brakes and assist conductors and enginemen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Cars parked by Conway Yards of Pennsylvania Railroad with trains in background, Conway, Pennsylvania
